               <msContents>
                  <summary>Antiphonary for the Fast of Lent, ጾመ፡ ድጓ፡, with musical notation</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1"><locus from="1r" to="97v" facs="003">Fols 1r–97v</locus><title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2361somade">Ṣoma dǝggʷā</title><incipit xml:lang="gez">በ፪ በማኅትወ፡ ድራረ፡ ጾም፡ ባኡ፡ ዘወረደ፡ እምላዕሉ፡ አይሁድ፡ ሰቀሉ፡ ወሚመ፡ ኢያእመሩ፡ እግዚአ፡ ኵሉ፡ <gap reason="omitted"/></incipit>
                  <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ‘ǝz</textLang>
                </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2"><locus from="97v" to="100v" facs="100">Fols 97v–100v</locus><title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2361somade#Haleta">Ṣoma dǝggʷā, Table
                                                  of melodic variations for the Hallelujah (,
                                                  ).</title>
                  <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ‘ǝz</textLang>

                  <colophon xml:id="coloph1">
                  <locus target="#100v" facs="103"> f. 100v, column 1</locus>
                  “Praise God who helped me to finish in peace, his servant Wäldä Aragawi, to finish this Ṣoma Dǝggwa and Halleluiatic chants of Yared, the wise priest, in the year of Luke the Evangelist, in the month Näḥase 1919 EC, thirty nights, twenty-sixth day in the reign of our Empress Askalä Maryam [Zewditu].”
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ይትባረክ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ዘአፈጸመኒ፡ በሰላም፡ ለገብራ፡ ወልደ፡ አረጋዊ፡ ጾመ፡ ድጓ፡ ወአንቀጽ፡ ሃሌታ፡ ጥበበ፡ ያሬድ፡ ካህን፡። እንዘ፡ ወንጌላዊ፡ ሉቃስ፡ በውርኃ፡ ነሐሴ፡ ፲ወ፱፻፲ወ፱ ዓመተ፡ ምሕረት፡ በ፴ሌሊት፡ ወበ፳፮ መዓልት። በመዋዕሊሃ፡ ለንግሥት፡ አስካለ፡ ማርያም።</foreign>
                </colophon>


                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
